menu "espAGC canonical yaAGC socket (Task #18)"

config AGC_YAAGC_SOCKET
    bool "Route engine I/O through canonical SocketAPI semantics"
    default y
    help
        Route ChannelInput/Output/Routine through the canonical yaAGC
        SocketAPI port in components/yaagc_socket. The engine then
        exposes its channel-I/O surface as a TCP listener speaking the
        canonical 4-byte protocol — same path that yaAGC.exe uses on
        Pi/Linux, verified 5/5 on V37E00E×2 + working on hardware as
        of 2026-05-13.

        Default-y as of the canonical-port commit. The legacy
        channel_router pump_input path is preserved under `#ifndef
        CONFIG_AGC_YAAGC_SOCKET` for host Layer-2 tests; disable this
        Kconfig only if you need to A/B-test against that legacy
        behaviour. Hardware should always have it on.

        With this on, local sources (touch / web DSKY / peripheral_stub
        LM_INI) inject through a synthetic-client byte ring inside
        yaagc_socket, so the canonical mask+value drain handles them
        identically to TCP peer arrivals. The LCD/web mirror keeps
        working via channel_router_on_output which is still called
        unconditionally from ChannelOutput.

config AGC_YAAGC_SOCKET_PORT
    int "TCP port for yaAGC node listener"
    depends on AGC_YAAGC_SOCKET
    range 1024 65535
    default 19850
    help
        Port to bind on 0.0.0.0. windows_yaagc_test.py picks per-pid
        ports above 19850 against upstream yaAGC.exe; using 19850 here
        keeps test scripts identical between the two builds. Under
        QEMU forward this with -nic user,hostfwd=tcp::19850-:19850.

endmenu
